Vice President Mike Pence visited Camp Atterbury National Guard Base in Edinburgh, Indiana, to express his gratitude and support to the men and women serving in the Indiana National Guard. He commended their service and the sacrifices made by their families. Pence also extended the greetings and appreciation of President Donald Trump to the soldiers. He highlighted the administration's commitment to providing resources and support to the military, including the largest increase in national defense funding since the Reagan era and the largest pay raise for soldiers in over a decade. Pence acknowledged the significant role played by the National Guard, especially in the global war on terror, and praised the Indiana National Guard for their contributions. He also mentioned their involvement in disaster response efforts. Pence encouraged the soldiers to be prepared, vigilant, and to trust their superiors and orders. He assured them of the prayers and support of the people of Indiana and the nation as they prepare for deployment.